The paper discusses the use of Bayesian Networks for decision making in Intelligent Autonomous Vehicles (IAVs), which falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the need for testing Bayesian Network models in real situations, which suggests a focus on Robotics (cs.RO). The use of Bayesian Networks for decision making also involves machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV) techniques. Finally, the paper discusses the development of a general decision making framework for IAVs, which falls under the category of Systems and Control (cs.SY).
